Shopping local is always a topic near and dear to a community pharmacy's heart — and for good reason. When it comes to your health, choosing a local pharmacy over a large chain makes a genuine difference.

## You Get to Know Your Pharmacist

At a chain pharmacy, you might see a different pharmacist every time you visit. At a local pharmacy like TRS in Stafford, TX, you build a real relationship with your pharmacist. Dr. Haroon Waseem knows your medication history, your health conditions, and your goals — and he uses that knowledge every time you fill a prescription.

That relationship matters. Studies show that patients who have an ongoing relationship with a pharmacist are more adherent to their medications and have better health outcomes.

## Faster, More Personal Service

Large chain pharmacies serve hundreds of patients a day. Local pharmacies serve their community — and that means shorter wait times, more time to answer your questions, and a team that genuinely cares about getting your prescription right.

## Accessible Pricing

At TRS Pharmacy, we're a 501(c)(3) nonprofit. That means for self-pay patients, we offer our best possible pricing — acquisition cost plus a small dispensing fee. We also accept all major insurance plans, including Medicare Part D and Medicaid.

No insurance? Call us before you come in. We'll look up the best price available for your specific medication and give you a quote before you commit.

## Specialized Services Chains Don't Offer

TRS Pharmacy offers services you won't find at most chain pharmacies:

- **Pharmacogenomics (PGx) testing** — DNA-based precision medicine testing
- **Nutrient depletion analysis** — understanding how your medications affect your nutrition
- **Free prescription delivery** within 10 miles of Stafford, TX
- **Medication synchronization** — all your prescriptions aligned to one monthly fill date

## Supporting Your Community

When you fill a prescription at TRS Pharmacy, you're supporting a nonprofit organization dedicated to making healthcare accessible for everyone in Stafford, Sugar Land, Missouri City, and the greater Houston area.

